text within which the collection was made as well as the complex relationships between museums, anthropologists, and First Nations. Accessibly written and vigorously researched, First Nations, Museums, Narrations raises timely questions about the role of collections in the twenty-first century and considers the way forward for indigenous peoples and the museums that house their cultural treasures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAnthropologyzCanada, WesternxHistoryy20th century. 0aEthnological expeditionszCanada, WesternxHistoryy20th century. 0aEthnological museums and collectionsxPolitical aspectsxHistoryy20th century. 0aEthnological museums and collectionsxSocial aspectsxHistoryy20th century. 0aIndians of North AmericaxAntiquitiesxCollectors and collectingzCanada, WesternxHistoryy20th century. 0aIndigenous peoplesxAntiquitiesxCollectors and collectingzCanada, WesternxHistoryy20th century. 0aIndigenous peoplesxMuseumszGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aMuseums and IndianszGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aMuseumsxAcquisitionsxHistoryy20th century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Native American Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311141999240uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077482727040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774827270423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774827270/original  a978-3-11-127407-2  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-127709-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-141999-2  University of British Col